e quarter of all mammal species.</p><table border="0" width="100%">  <tr>    <td align="center"><p align="center">Click on the buttons below to learn more about the Chiroptera.</p><a href="chirofr.html"><img src="/images/buttonfruse.gif" width="130" height="80" border="0" alt="Fossil Record"></a><a href="chirolh.html"><img src="/images/buttonlhuse.gif" width="130" height="80" border="0" alt="Life & Ecology"></a><a href="chirosy.html"><img src="/images/buttonsyuse.gif" width="130" height="80" border="0" alt="Systematics"></a><a href="chiromm.html"><img src="/images/buttonmmuse.gif" width="130" height="80" border="0" alt="Morphology"></a></td>  </tr></table><hr width="60%"><table width="80%" border="0" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" align="center">  <tr><td><a href="/vertebrates/flight/enter.html"><img src="/subway/specicons/dimorphsmall.gif" width="83" height="59" alt="Vertebrate Flight"></a></td>    <td><b>UCMP Special Exhibit: <a href="/vertebrates/flight/enter.html">Vertebrate Flight</a></b><br>Want to learn more about flight? What do a pterosaur, a bat, and a bird have incommon? How do we know they evolved flight independently? Find out for yourself!</td>  </tr></table><p>To learn much more about bats &#151; from their scientific names to how to keepthem out of your belfry &#151; visit the informative <a href="http://www.batcon.org/">BatConservation International</a> site.</p><p align="center"><a href="/help/WebLiftComb.map"><img src="/images/WebLiftComb.gif" ISMAP border="0"></a></p><p align="center"><a href="auchiroptera.html"><img src="/images/authors.gif" width="68" height="23" hspace="3" alt="Authors"></a><a href="/copyright.html"><img src="/images/copyright.gif" width="23" height="23" hspace="3" alt="Copyright"></a></p></td>  </tr></table><!--#include virtual="/footer1.html"--><!--#include virtual="/sitesearch.html"--></body></html> contentType 9 text/html url 61 https://ucmp.berkeley.edu:443/mammal/eutheria/